-- Belmont Upsets No. 12 North Carolina in Men’s College Basketball
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2013-11-18T05:02:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-18/belmont-upsets-no-12-north-carolina-in-men-s-college-basketball.html
Belmont University upset 12th-ranked
North Carolina 83-80 in college basketball’s Hall of Fame Tipoff
tournament, while Iowa State upset seventh-ranked Michigan 77-70
with a game-ending 23-10 scoring run.  J.J. Mann scored 28 points for Nashville, Tennessee-based
Belmont, including a go-ahead three-pointer with 13.1 seconds
left yesterday in  Chapel Hill , North Carolina. It was the
Bruins’ first win over a top-25 ranked opponent since 2003.  Indiana State also pulled off an upset yesterday, beating
21st-ranked Notre Dame 83-70 in South Bend, Indiana.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  